[Course_Description]
Being bored is something of a novelty in the age of smartphones. And in his 2017 book, Bored and Brilliant, Manoush Zomorodi posits that this lack of boredom in our lives can actually zap us of our creativity. In this audiobook summary, get bite-sized tips that can help you alter your digital habits to enhance your innate creativity. Learn how the convenience of the internet has changed how we think and act, how to unplug and use technology in a healthy way, and more. Each easily digestible point is drawn from Bored and Brilliant, allowing you to glean some of the book's most poignant lessons on the go. Note: This audiobook summary was produced by Blinkist. We are pleased to host this content in our library.